PROBLEM1

\(var(Y_{ij})=var(\mu+b_i+e_{ij})\) \(=var(b_i)+var(e_{ij})\) \(={\sigma_b}^2+{\sigma_e}^2\)

\(cov(Y_{ij},Y_{ik}) = E[(Y_{ij}-\mu_{ij})(Y_{ik}-\mu_{ik})]\) \(=E(b_i+e_{ij})(b_i+e_{ik})\) \(=E({b_i}^2+e_{ij}*e_{ik}+b_i*e_{ik}+b_i*e_{ij})\) \(=E({b_i}^2)+E(e_{ij}*e_{ik})+E(b_i*e_{ik})+E(b_i*e_{ij})\) \(=E(b_i^2)\) \(=(Eb_i)^2+var(b_i)\) \(=\sigma_b^2\)

\(corr(Y_{ij},Y_{ik})=\frac{cov(Y_{ij},Y_{ik})}{\sqrt{ var(Y_{ij})*var(Y_{ik})}}\)

\(={\sigma_b}^2/({\sigma_b}^2+{\sigma_e}^2)\)

PROBLEM 2

2.1

ggplot(dental_df, aes(x = age, y = distance, group = child)) + geom_line(aes(color = gender))

2.2

\(E(Y_{ij})=\beta_0+\beta_1*age_{ij}\) \(var(Y_{ij})=var(a_i)+var(b_k)+var(e_{ij})\) \(={\sigma_a}^2+{\sigma_b}^2+{\sigma_e}^2\)
